<TITLE> BNP to run CCC polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 16 (bdnews24.com)  Two BNP stalwarts from Chittagong have begun a closed-door meeting with chief Khaleda Zia after a two-and-a-half hour meeting of the opposition party's policymaking standing committee. The meeting of the BNP top brass, which began at 9pm on Sunday, decided that the opposition party would take part in the Chittagong City Corporation elections slated for June 17. Standing committee member Mahbubur Rahman told bdnews24.com after the policy-level meeting that BNP believed in elections. Regarding the CCC polls, he said, "We will take part." 
